reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I'm So Glad I Swapped My Muddy Yard For This Lifelike Artificial Grass
reviews.reviewText: As a pet owner with two messy labradoodles, my yard has been utterly destroyed from years of digging, bathroom breaks, and zoomies. While I love letting them roam free outdoors, the muddy slosh and huge dead grass patches were an eyesore. Instead of constantly reseeding, I decided to install this handy artificial turf grass rug - and my pups now have their own posh potty patio!I absolutely love how real this synthetic grass looks with its springy blade texture and rich emerald hue. The 0.8 inch blade height perfectly mimics a lush lawn, inviting paws for a rollick. Being UV-resistant and weatherproof, it maintains its vibrant color despite heavy use.Another bonus is the woven drainage holes which prevent urine puddles from pooling or stenches lingering. I just occasionally rinse it with the garden hose to keep the potty patch refreshed. So much easier than dealing with fertilizer and mud!Whether they're sunbathing, chasing squirrels, or doing their business, my dogs are obsessed with their new grass rug hangout. And I no longer cringe seeing brown patches ruining my lawn! For hassle-free, realistic turf that your pets will love, this is a phenomenal solution. It's the ultimate pet-friendly lawn substitute!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Handy artificial turf mat!
reviews.reviewText: Great size artificial turf mat! Perfect for outdoors, nice grass like resemblance, UV resistant and come with drainage holes. When receiving, it will need a bit fluffed up as the the grass strands are a bit matted from shipping. I placed mine out in an area of my yard that leads into a rock walkway, but always tends to get muddy. Drives me nuts. I have other areas of the yard that we have pieces of artificial turf left over from when we got the front yard covered and found that they do a nice job in helping over areas that can get muddy sometimes. Less messy, slippery and helps prevent mud coming into the house from the dogs tracking in. So definitely handy on rainy days. Like that it is cut-able, to fit your area perfectly. Backing seems pretty durable and has drainage holes so water or urine doesn't pool up. Not as thick as professional turf, but a great alternative for the cost. Easy to spray down and keep fresh smelling. Overall, I'm happy with the quality of this artificial turf mat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Transforming my balcony into a lush green oasis has been a dream, and the Fake Grass Turf Carpet has made it a reality. This product has exceeded my expectations in terms of quality, appearance, and ease of installation.Let's start with the appearance. The turf carpet mimics the look and feel of real grass remarkably well. Its vibrant green color adds a refreshing touch to my balcony, creating a serene and inviting outdoor space. The texture is soft and comfortable underfoot, making it perfect for lounging or enjoying barefoot walks.Installation was a breeze. The carpet comes in a roll, all I had to do was roll it out. The backing is durable and provides a stable base, ensuring the carpet stays in place even in windy conditions. No need for messy soil, watering, or mowing—just roll out the carpet, and voila, instant greenery!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Izzy Approved Artificial Grass Pad for Patio!
reviews.reviewText: This is a great fake grass matt that our fur baby, Izzy, loves! We have a large patio that Izzy loves to spend time on when we are enjoying it, especially in the evening. She comes out with us and will sit, but not lay down on the hard cement. This grassy rug was the perfect solution. She not only will sit on it, but is comfortable stretching out on it as well. It came in a tight roll, but easily flattened out in a couple of days outside. It also has drainage holes in the anti-slip backing to allow it to dry after a rain or cleaning. Izzy recommends giving it five stars!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My dog loves it!
reviews.reviewText: When I received this pad, it was rolled up and had a kink to the roll at the end of the pad. I placed the pad on the floor and put the box on the kinked area to let it flatten. (It took a few days to flatten.) My dog walked over, gave it a sniff, and laid down on it. He and my other two dogs love it. It is not very thick, so if you are looking for a thick, heavy pad, this isn't the one. But if you are looking for a lightweight pad that feels like grass for your dogs, this one is perfect.
